in characters of <em>Karma</em> will be played by <em><a href="https://www.nme.com/series/squid-game">Squid Game</a></em> &#39;s Park Hae-soo, <em><a href="https://www.nme.com/series/hometown-cha-cha-cha">Hometown Cha-Cha-Cha</a></em> &#39;s Shin Min-a, Lee Hee-jun from <em><a href="https://www.nme.com/series/a-killer-paradox">A Killer Paradox</a> ,</em> veteran actor Kim Sung-kyun, <em><a href="https://www.nme.com/series/running-man">Running Man</a></em> star Lee Kwang-soo as well as <em>The First Responders</em> actress Gong Seung-yeon.</p><h2> Is there a trailer for Netflix&#39;s <em>Karma</em> ?</h2><p> On March 27, Netflix dropped a promotional clip starring the show&#39;s ensemble cast reenacting their lines from the series, quotes selected to sum up the personalities and motivations of their respective characters. </p><p><iframe loading="lazy" title="Six actors, six dramatic character reenactments |业力| Netflix [ENG SUB]" width="696" height="392" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/KSNvYEkLIn8?feature=oembed&enablejsapi=1" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen></iframe></p><p> Netflix dropped the show&#39;s official trailer on March 19, which begins with a shot of a man receiving a letter in the mail. Upon opening the envelope, he finds a certificate of insurance, which states that the payout will be given to the immediate family of the insured. The man tells a mercenary that he needs his father killed, in order to receive the insurance payout. </p><p><iframe loading="lazy" title="业力|官方预告片| Netflix [ENG SUB]" width="696" height="392" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/E_e9cpN994s?feature=oembed&enablejsapi=1" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen></iframe></p><p> On March 4, the streamer released a new teaser for the series. The brutal new clip features the show&#39;s six main characters and the sheer intensity of their karmic bond to one another following a mysterious accident. </p><p><iframe loading="lazy" title="业力|官方预告片| Netflix [ENG SUB]" width="696" height="392" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/8_yFpaWFm7c?feature=oembed&enablejsapi=1" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen></iframe></p><h2> <em>How to watch the new Netflix K-drama</em> ?</h2><p> <em>Karma</em> is set to make an exclusive premiere on Netflix on April 4.</p><p> The post <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/tv/karma-netflix-k-drama-trailer-cast-plot-more-park-hae-soo-shin-min-a-3843327">Park Hae-soo, Shin Min-a and more preview their characters for new Netflix K-drama &#39;Karma&#39;</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
